    title: 'Training the whole family',
    body: 'As a dog parent, your role goes beyond just training your dog — you’re also teaching the rest of your family how to help. Everyone in the household needs to be on the same page when it comes to setting rules and encouraging positive behaviour. It’s especially important to create an environment where teasing, bullying or inconsistent training are avoided. The key is motivating every family member to stick to the plan and help train the dog consistently.',
  },
  {
