---

<Base
  title="Free DIY Puppy Training Course | The Fairy Tails K9 Centre"
  description="Our free DIY puppy course: four structured weeks of socialisation, life skills and husbandry, a daily schedule and a toilet-training guide from our trainers."
  path="/puppycourse"
  updated="2026-07-16"
  ogImage={`${business.domain}${ogHero.src}`}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(jsonLd)} is:inline />

  <div data-page="puppycourse">
    <!-- ============ HERO ============ -->
    <section class="relative isolate flex min-h-[92svh] items-end overflow-hidden bg-pine-950" data-hero>
      <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 overflow-hidden">
        <Image
          src={heroPup}
          alt="A young puppy in a pink harness sitting on a sunny country lane"
          class="h-full w-full object-cover object-[50%_35%]"
          widths={[768, 1280, 1920]}
          sizes="100vw"
          loading="eager"
          fetchpriority="high"
          decoding="async"
          data-hero-media
        />
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-pine-950/95 via-pine-950/50 to-pine-950/25"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-4 pb-24 pt-36 sm:pb-28">
        <p class="eyebrow text-honey-300" data-hero-eyebrow>Free course · Do it yourself at home</p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-3xl font-display text-[2.6rem] font-bold leading-[1.05] text-cream-50 sm:text-6xl" data-hero-title>
          <span class="hero-line block">The DIY</span>
          <span class="hero-line block"><em class="squiggle not-italic">Puppy Course</em></span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-cream-100/90" data-hero-sub>
          Everything you need to raise a calm, confident puppy — socialisation, toilet training,
          sleep, life skills and more. Four structured weeks, written by our trainers, free to
          every puppy parent.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap gap-4" data-hero-cta>
          <a href="#start" class="btn btn-honey">
            Start the course <span class="btn-arrow" aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
          </a>
          <a href={business.acuity.freeConsult} class="btn btn-ghost-light">Talk to a trainer — free</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="absolute bottom-6 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 text-cream-100/70" data-hero-cue aria-hidden="true">
        <svg width="22" height="30" viewBox="0 0 22 30" fill="none" class="animate-bounce">
          <rect x="1" y="1" width="20" height="28" rx="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"></rect>
          <circle cx="11" cy="10" r="3" fill="currentColor"></circle>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Trust strip — overlaps the hero -->
    <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto -mt-12 max-w-5xl px-4" data-hero-trust>
      <ul class="grain grid gap-4 rounded-2xl bg-cream-50 px-7 py-6 text-sm font-bold text-bark-700 shadow-[var(--shadow-polaroid)] sm:grid-cols-2 sm:gap-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
        <li class="paw-bullet flex items-center text-moss-700">100% free — no sign-up, no catch</li>
        <li class="paw-bullet flex items-center text-moss-700">Force-free &amp; science-backed</li>
        <li class="paw-bullet flex items-center text-moss-700">Four structured weeks</li>
        <li class="paw-bullet flex items-center text-moss-700">Written by our qualified trainers</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- ============ AIMS ============ -->
    <section id="start" class="mx-auto max-w-6xl scroll-mt-24 px-4 py-20 sm:py-28" data-section="aims">
      <div class="grid items-center gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1.1fr_0.9fr]">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow text-honey-700" data-reveal>What you'll cover</p>
          <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold text-moss-800 sm:text-4xl" data-reveal>
            The aims of <em class="squiggle not-italic">the course</em>
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-bark-700" data-reveal>
            Puppies learn fastest in their first few months — and the habits you build now last a
            lifetime. Over four weeks, this course walks you through:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-2.5" data-stagger>
            {
              aims.map((aim) => (
                <li class="rounded-full border-2 border-moss-200 bg-cream-100 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-bold text-moss-800 transition-colors duration-200 hover:border-honey-400 hover:bg-honey-200/40">
                  {aim}
                </li>
              ))
            }
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-7 text-bark-700" data-reveal>
            Work through it at your puppy's pace — and if you get stuck,
            <a href="#enquire" class="font-bold text-moss-700 underline decoration-honey-400 decoration-2 underline-offset-4">ask us anything</a>.
            It's what we're here for.
          </p>
        </div>
        <figure class="polaroid mx-auto w-full max-w-sm" style="transform: rotate(2deg);" data-reveal>
          <Image
            src={goldenPup}
            alt="A golden retriever puppy sitting attentively"
            class="aspect-[4/5] w-full rounded-[2px] bg-cream-100 object-cover"
            widths={[480, 960]}
            sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 24rem, 90vw"
          />
          <figcaption class="px-1 pt-3 text-center font-display text-sm font-bold text-bark-700">
            Start them young — but there's never a wrong time
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============ METHODS ============ -->
    <section class="bg-cream-100" data-section="methods">
      <HillDivider class="bg-cream-50 text-cream-100" />
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pb-20 pt-12 sm:pb-28">
        <p class="eyebrow text-honey-700" data-reveal>Our methods</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 max-w-2xl font-display text-3xl font-bold text-moss-800 sm:text-4xl" data-reveal>
          How we'll train — <em class="squiggle not-italic">kindly</em>
        </h2>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-bark-700" data-reveal>
            <p>
              Positive reinforcement training, in conjunction with management methods, is the
              simplest and most current training method. It is the one we will use to guide you —
              allow us to explain why we have confidence in it.
            </p>
            <p>
              More excellent dogs, more happy humans! The reward-based technique of positive
              reinforcement training has been scientifically demonstrated to effectively encourage
              the behaviours you want your puppy to exhibit, and to instil confidence in them when
              entering a new environment. To put it plainly: greater incentives result in more
              positive behaviour.
            </p>
            <p>
              When we say "good behaviour", we may mean anything — having our puppies sit, lie
              down, settle, or return when we call their name.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div data-reveal>
            <div class="grain rounded-2xl bg-cream-50 p-7 shadow-[var(--shadow-lift)]">
              <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-moss-800">Rewards can take several forms</h3>
              <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2.5 text-bark-700">
                <li class="paw-bullet flex items-start">Treats</li>
                <li class="paw-bullet flex items-start">Toys</li>
                <li class="paw-bullet flex items-start">Praise</li>
                <li class="paw-bullet flex items-start">…or anything else your dog enjoys</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-bark-500">
                However, let's not make it about money — that has not worked out well for humans.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="mt-14 font-display text-2xl font-bold text-moss-800" data-reveal>
          Management methods in training
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed text-bark-700" data-reveal>
          Management is about regulating the setting and surroundings around your puppy to keep
          them from making errors or getting themselves into trouble. You may believe management
          makes you look like the fun police — the reality is quite the reverse. It helps them
          become acquainted with the rights and wrongs by setting them up for success, rather than
          learning by trial and error. A few ways to practise it:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-7 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3" data-stagger>
          {
            management.map((m) => (
              <article class="rounded-2xl border-2 border-cream-200 bg-cream-50 p-7 transition-colors duration-300 hover:border-moss-300">
                <h4 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-moss-700">{m.title}</h4>
                <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-bark-700">{m.body}</p>
              </article>
            ))
          }
        </div>

        <!-- Straight talk: punishment -->
        <div class="grain mt-12 rounded-3xl bg-pine-900 p-8 sm:p-10" data-reveal>
          <p class="eyebrow text-honey-400">Straight talk — the use of punishment</p>
          <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-cream-100">
            Punishment may get you quick results for a behaviour, but it will also create
            generalised anxiety, fears, phobias, and a lack of confidence to cope with the wider
            world. It can lead to an anxious or reactive dog. That's why nothing in this course —
            and nothing in our school — ever relies on it.
          </p>
